## First Person Mode (Opinion Mode) + POV Spine (Phoenix Raising)\
\
This system has a production \'93first person mode\'94 that is implemented as 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 opinion_mode=True
\f0\fs32 \cb7  plus an optional 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 pov_spine
\f0\fs32 \cb7  payload. The goal is to produce a controlled first-person author voice (memoir-like, experience-framed), without drifting into practitioner/case-study voice.\
\
### What it is\
\
- **
\f8\fs28 \cb10 opinion_mode
\f0\fs32 \cb7 **: A mode flag that changes narrative voice expectations.\
- **POV spine (
\f8\fs28 \cb10 pov_spine
\f0\fs32 \cb7 )**: A structured set of first-person voice anchors used to keep first-person passages consistent and credible.\
\
The POV spine structure (canonical fields):\
\
- 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 belief
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
- 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 former_belief
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
- 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 tension
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
- 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 refusal
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
- 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 cost_paid
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
- 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 boundary
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
\
### Where it is configured / passed through\
\
- **Phoenix Raising generator**: 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 SOURCE_OF_TRUTH/tools/phoenix_raising_creator.py
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
  - 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 PhoenixRaisingCreator.__init__(..., opinion_mode: bool = False, pov_spine: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None)
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
- **POV spine generation/validation utilities**:\
  - 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 phoenix_ui/utils/pov_spine_generator.py
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
    - 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 POVSpineGenerator.generate_from_author(...)
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
    - 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 validate_pov_spine_with_author(...)
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
  - 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 phoenix_ui/utils/opinion_validator.py
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
    - 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 OpinionModeValidator.validate_complete_setup(...)
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
\
### Deterministic distribution: first-person vs composite story parts\
\
In Phoenix Raising, opinion/first-person mode affects **story voice**, not story placement.\
\
The key rule is a deterministic mix of first-person and composite storytelling:\
\
- **Chapter 1**: all story layers are forced first-person (L1/L2/L3) when 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 opinion_mode=True
\f0\fs32 \cb7 .\
- **Chapters 2..N**:\
  - 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 L1
\f0\fs32 \cb7  and 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 L3
\f0\fs32 \cb7  are first-person in ~30% of chapters (deterministic)\
  - 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 L2
\f0\fs32 \cb7  is always composite (unless Chapter 1 override)\
\
Implementation:\
\
- 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 PhoenixRaisingCreator._opinion_first_person_flags(chapter_num, num_chapters)
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
  - For the canonical 12-chapter arc:\
    - 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 L1
\f0\fs32 \cb7  first-person in chapters 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 \{2, 6, 10\}
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
    - 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 L3
\f0\fs32 \cb7  first-person in chapters 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 \{2, 4, 8, 12\}
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
  - For other chapter counts:\
    - Approximates 30% via stable hashing.\
\
### How first-person content is produced (fallback)\
\
If 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 opinion_mode=True
\f0\fs32 \cb7  and the current chapter/layer is flagged first-person, Phoenix Raising can generate a deterministic first-person story chunk directly from the POV spine:\
\
- 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 PhoenixRaisingCreator._build_opinion_first_person_story_text(...)
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
  - Uses POV spine fields (
\f8\fs28 \cb10 former_belief
\f0\fs32 \cb7 , 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 belief
\f0\fs32 \cb7 , 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 cost_paid
\f0\fs32 \cb7 , 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 boundary
\f0\fs32 \cb7 ) plus light scaffolding.\
  - Produces a memoir-like first-person block.\
  - Avoids \'93practitioner case study\'94 language.\
  - Marks the generated story with metadata:\
    - 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 metadata.category = "first_person"
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
    - 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 metadata.truth_level = "author"
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
\
### Opinion-mode enforcement points (voice safety)\
\
Phoenix Raising applies additional voice constraints under 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 opinion_mode=True
\f0\fs32 \cb7 :\
\
- **Hard filter: block practitioner case-study voice**\
  - 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 PhoenixRaisingCreator._contains_practitioner_case_study_language(text)
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
  - Used during story selection retries to avoid \'93I worked with a client/patient\'85\'94 style voice.\
\
- **Replace practitioner-framed author paragraphs in prose body**\
  - In 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 _assemble_chapter_with_beats
\f0\fs32 \cb7  (prose hydration stage), when 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 opinion_mode
\f0\fs32 \cb7  and 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 pov_spine
\f0\fs32 \cb7  are present, the system replaces common practitioner-framed paragraphs with a POV-spine \'93micro-story\'94 assembled from:\
    - 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 former_belief
\f0\fs32 \cb7 , 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 cost_paid
\f0\fs32 \cb7 , 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 belief
\f0\fs32 \cb7 , 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 boundary
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
\
### Relationship to Narrative Flow opinion mode (atoms)\
\
The broader system also has opinion mode support in the Narrative Flow orchestrator (atom pipeline):\
\
- 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 OPINION_MODE_NARRATIVE_FLOW_IMPLEMENTATION.md
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
- 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 cluster_therapy_tok/runtime/orchestrator.py
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
  - Opinion atoms: 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 opinion_\{atom_type\}
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
  - Fallback transform: 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 _transform_to_opinion()
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
  - Validation: 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 _validate_opinion_atom()
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
\
Phoenix Raising (CSV pipeline) and Narrative Flow (atom pipeline) both use the same conceptual \'93opinion/first-person\'94 contract, but enforce it in different places.\
\
### How to verify first person mode is working\
\
- **Input verification**\
  - 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 opinion_mode=True
\f0\fs32 \cb7  is set for the run.\
  - 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 pov_spine
\f0\fs32 \cb7  is present and complete (6 required fields), or you accept reduced strength.\
\
- **Manifest / chapter metadata checks**\
  - Look for story objects where 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 metadata.category == "first_person"
\f0\fs32 \cb7  and IDs like 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 opinion_fp_<chapter>_<layer>
\f0\fs32 \cb7 .\
\
- **Text output checks**\
  - First-person layers contain clear 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 I ...
\f0\fs32 \cb7  voice and POV-spine phrasing.\
  - Practitioner/case-study phrases are absent (e.g., \'93my client\'94, \'93in my practice\'94, \'93I worked with someone\'94).\
\
\
### Banned Content Lists & Safety Policies\
\
**QA Harness Banned Lists (v1):**\
- **Minor**: AI self-references ("As an AI", "language model", "ChatGPT", etc.)\
- **Major**: Immersion-breaking phrases ("I don't have feelings"), generic filler ("Furthermore"), clinical language\
- **Critical**: Harmful content, illegal activities, explicit medical/legal claims, financial guarantees\
\
**Duplicate Allowlist:**\
- Common therapeutic phrases allowed to repeat: "Take a deep breath.", "It's okay to feel this way.", etc.\
\
**Multilingual Safety Post-Checks:**\
- **English**: Detects claims like "cure", "guarantee", "clinically proven", "medical/legal advice"\
- **Chinese (Simplified/Traditional)**: Corresponding patterns: 
