## Phase 1-3 Implementation: Complete Book Variety System (2026-01-11)\
\
This section documents the complete three-phase implementation that transforms Phoenix Raising from a single-template system to a flexible, product-ready book generation engine with deterministic variety, structural routing, and optional module extensions.\
\
### Phase 1: Protocol Slot Loader (Topic-Scoped Slot Variables)\
\
**Purpose**: Inject deterministic, topic-scoped slot variables into the hydration pipeline before template rendering.\
\
#### Implementation\
- **File**: 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 SOURCE_OF_TRUTH/data/config/gen_z_phoenix_protocol_slot_variables.csv
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
- **Loader**: 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 PhoenixRaisingCreator._load_gen_z_protocol_bank()
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
- **Injector**: 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 PhoenixRaisingCreator._inject_protocol_slots()
\f0\fs32 \cb7 \
\
#### Key Features\
- **Deterministic selection**: Uses 
\f8\fs28 \cb10 md5(book_seed|topic|slot_variable)
\f0\fs32 \cb7  for consistent variant selection\
- **Topic-scoped variants**: Each slot variable has multiple variants per topic\
- **Global enrichment**: Applies to all books regardless of structure family or modules\
- **Backward compatibility**: No impact when CSV is missing or empty\
\
#### Usage\

\f8 python\
# Automatic injection happens before template hydration\
slot_values = creator._inject_protocol_slots(slot_values, topic, book_seed)
